.SS "Callback Information"
The Callback structure is SgDropPocketCallbackStruct.
A pointer to the following structure is passed to each callback:
.sS
.iS
.ta .25i 1.1i
typedef struct
{
	\*Lint		\*Vreason\*L;
	\*LXEvent	\*V* event\*L;
	\*LWindow	\*Vwindow\*L;
	\*LXmString	\*ViconName\*L;
	\*Lchar *	\*ViconData\*L;
} SgDropPocketCallbackStruct;
.iE
.sE
.VL 1i 
.LI "\*Vreason\*O"
Indicates why the callback was invoked.  The constant
\*LSgCR_ICON_CHANGE\*O is the reason associated with callbacks
generated by a successful icon drop on the DropPocket.
.LI "\*Vevent\*O"
Points to the \*LXEvent\*O that triggered the callback
.LI "\*Vwindow\*O"
Specifies the window of the DropPocket.
.LI "\*ViconName\*O"
Specifies the name of the icon.  For icons representing files, this is
the file name.  For other types of icons, the name may not completely
specify the icon.  For example a person icon may have the name jake,
but the icon represents a person in /usr/lib/faces/jake.
.LI "\*ViconData\*O"
The full string description of the icon.
.LE 
.SS "Translations"
.ne 15
SgDropPocket includes translations from Primitive.
The SgDropPocket translations are listed below.
These translations may not directly correspond to a
translation table.
.iS
.ta 1.5i
Enter:	Enter()
Leave:	Leave()
.wH .fi
.iE
.SS "Action Routines"
The SgDropPocket action routines are described below:
.VL
.LI "\*LEnter()\*O:"
When the pointer enters the DropPocket, this action highlights the
icon and changes the background color if the pointer contains a
droppable icon.
.nL
.ne 5
.LI "\*LLeave()\*O:"
This unhighlights the icon and resets the background color when the
pointer leaves the DropPocket.
.LE
